  "section_name": "Financial Analysis",
  "text": "R&D investment intensity in Q4 2025 was 17.73% of revenue (K007), with R&D expenses of $1,098,000,000 (C016) on revenue of $6,194,000,000 (C010). This compares to $1,088,000,000 in Q3 2025 (C024), $1,082,000,000 in Q2 2025 (C032), and $1,110,000,000 in Q1 2026 (C008), suggesting sustained commitment to product development despite revenue fluctuations. The consistent R&D spending level, representing approximately one-sixth of revenue, indicates Adobe prioritizes innovation and product enhancement, which is critical for maintaining competitive positioning in the creative software and digital experience markets.",
